1.	Explain how you can use CSS and JavaScript in your Django web application.

In a Django web application, CSS and JavaScript can be used to enhance the frontend:
    1.	Static Files: Store CSS and JavaScript files in the static directory.
    2.	Include in Templates: Use the {% static %} template tag to reference CSS and JavaScript files in your HTML templates:
    3.	Django Forms: Inject JavaScript or use CSS for styling Django forms.


